  "original_title": "\u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1\u0bcd\u0bb1\u0bcb\u0bb2\u0bc8 \u0baa\u0bc6\u0bb1 \u0bae\u0bc1\u0b9f\u0bbf\u0baf\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bb2\u0bcd \u0baa\u0bcb\u0b95\u0bb2\u0bbe\u0bae\u0bcd",
  "text_idx": {
    "en": {
      "title": "May not be able to get birth oil",
      "author": "unknown",
      "body_lines": [
        "The World Food Program has indicated that the Sri Lankan government may not be able to obtain enough fuel for daily needs as the government restricts fuel imports for the next 12 months.",
        "As a result, the World Food Program predicts that the ability of Sri Lankans to find or go to work will be reduced and the normal functioning of schools and public services will be disrupted.",
        "The World Food Program has reported that 6.3 million Sri Lankans are food insecure and this number is likely to rise further, indicating that 6.7 million Sri Lankans do not eat acceptable food.",
        "The World Food Program reported that because of the high cost of food and consumer goods, Sri Lankans have become accustomed to purchasing food and consumer goods in very small quantities and this has led to an increase in Sri Lankan visits to shops.",
        "The report indicated that the prices of nutritious foods and vegetables have increased by two to five times what they were before the economic crisis.",
        "The report also noted that Sri Lanka's expenditure on food imports has decreased from US$130 million to US$50 million per month.",
        "For Sri Lanka, USD 20.74 million has been donated to the World Food Programme, the statement said.",
        "But to help 3.4 million Sri Lankans from July to December, the World Food Program needs US$63 million and is reported to have a shortfall of US$42.3 million."
      ],
